[description]
Berlin (Mengenlehre) Uhr

A model to visualize the time according to the ideas of D. Binninger.
The original clock was placed on Kurfuerstendamm (near Uhlandstr.)
and is now relocated to the Europa Center.

The timedisplay is as follows:
top (round) 1 second
top row of rectangles (red) from left to right: 5, 10, 15, 20 hours
2nd row of rectangles (red) from left to right: 1, 2, 3, 4 hours
3rd row of rectangles from left to right (mostly yellow):
5, 10, 15(red), 20, 25, 30(red), 35, 40, 45(red), 50, 55 minutes
4th row of rectangles (yellow) from left to right: 1, 2, 3, 4 minutes

To get the time you have to add the values.

Input Signals:
one second
minute 1
minute 2
minute 3
minute 4
minute 5
minute 10
minute 15
minute 20
